JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 135
IS  - 3
SP  - 1681
EP  - 1724
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We introduce a simple method of recovering attention costs from choice data. Our method rests on a precise analogy with production theory. Costs of attention determine consumer demand and consumer welfare, just as a competitive firm’s technology determines its supply curve and profits. We implement our recovery method experimentally, outline applications, and link our work to the broader literature on inattention and mistaken decisions.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjaa011
